abstract: His interest in hearing directly from Mr. Bolton has made the Utah Republican one of the most closely-watched lawmakers.
snippet: His interest in hearing directly from Mr. Bolton has made the Utah Republican one of the most closely-watched lawmakers.
lead_paragraph: Senator Mitt Romney of Utah, one of the Republicans who has been most outspoken about his desire to hear from John R. Bolton, outlined his questions for the president’s defense team as Wednesday’s session got underway.

headline_main: Romney releases questions for White House lawyers and impeachment managers.

abstract: She was joined by Senators Lisa Murkowski and Mitt Romney.
snippet: She was joined by Senators Lisa Murkowski and Mitt Romney.
lead_paragraph: Senator Susan Collins, Republican of Maine, became the first senator outside of leadership to speak on the Senate floor during President Trump’s impeachment trial, when she rose to offer a question on behalf of three Republican centrists who have expressed interest in having witnesses: Senator Lisa Murkowski of Alaska, Mitt Romney of Utah and herself.

headline_main: Susan Collins submits first question of the trial on behalf of centrist Republicans.

abstract: In the final days before the caucuses, Ms. Warren is taking on the electability question in ads, on the stump and on her campaign bus, urging voters to embrace “courage over cynicism” and “hope over fear.”
snippet: In the final days before the caucuses, Ms. Warren is taking on the electability question in ads, on the stump and on her campaign bus, urging voters to embrace “courage over cynicism” and “hope over fear.”
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — The last time Senator Elizabeth Warren trundled across Iowa in a specially decorated campaign vehicle, an R.V. headed to the Iowa State Fair in August, it was wrapped with a cheeky play on the slogan for her sweeping agenda: “Honk if you’re ready for big, structural change!”

abstract: Republican lawmakers in Kansas pushed a proposed anti-abortion amendment to the state constitution through the state Senate on Wednesday even as abortion rights advocates argued that it would lead to a ban on most abortions like a measure being pursued in Tennessee.
snippet: Republican lawmakers in Kansas pushed a proposed anti-abortion amendment to the state constitution through the state Senate on Wednesday even as abortion rights advocates argued that it would lead to a ban on most abortions like a measure being pu...
lead_paragraph: TOPEKA, Kan. — Republican lawmakers in Kansas pushed a proposed anti-abortion amendment to the state constitution through the state Senate on Wednesday even as abortion rights advocates argued that it would lead to a ban on most abortions like a measure being pursued in Tennessee.
headline_main: Kansas Abortion Measure Advances in Tennessee Plan's Shadow
headline_print_headline: Kansas Abortion Measure Advances in Tennessee Plan's Shadow

abstract: In a letter last week to John R. Bolton, White House officials reviewing his book warned him not to publish it.
snippet: In a letter last week to John R. Bolton, White House officials reviewing his book warned him not to publish it.
lead_paragraph: The White House sent a letter last week to the former national security adviser John R. Bolton warning him against publication of his upcoming book, which includes details about the pressure campaign on Ukraine that led to President Trump’s impeachment, two White House officials said.
headline_main: White House is seeking to block Bolton book.

abstract: When President Donald Trump signed a revamped trade agreement with Mexico and Canada into law Wednesday, he kept a campaign pledge to improve upon a deal that he had long condemned.
snippet: When President Donald Trump signed a revamped trade agreement with Mexico and Canada into law Wednesday, he kept a campaign pledge to improve upon a deal that he had long condemned.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When President Donald Trump signed a revamped trade agreement with Mexico and Canada into law Wednesday, he kept a campaign pledge to improve upon a deal that he had long condemned.
headline_main: What Trump's New North American Trade Deal Actually Does
headline_print_headline: What Trump's New North American Trade Deal Actually Does

abstract: Republicans and Democrats plan to use their question period to question the leaders of the two opposing teams.
snippet: Republicans and Democrats plan to use their question period to question the leaders of the two opposing teams.
lead_paragraph: Momentum appears to be flagging for calling new witnesses in President Trump’s impeachment trial, but senators in both parties have signaled they will try to turn the questioning period into an opportunity turn the leaders of each legal team into fact witnesses.
headline_main: Will the senators try to turn the lawyers into witnesses?

abstract: Senator Doug Jones Alabama added, however, that President Trump’s own behavior is strengthening the obstruction case.
snippet: Senator Doug Jones Alabama added, however, that President Trump’s own behavior is strengthening the obstruction case.
lead_paragraph: In the first hint of a possible crack in Democratic unity, Senator Doug Jones, Democrat of Alabama, suggested Wednesday that he might vote to acquit President Trump on the charge of obstruction of Congress, though he said Mr. Trump’s own behavior is strengthening the case.

headline_main: Democrat considers voting to acquit Trump of obstruction.

abstract: The proposal, three years in the making, favored Israeli priorities and was conceived without Palestinian input. Here are the main points and some of the most contested elements.
snippet: The proposal, three years in the making, favored Israeli priorities and was conceived without Palestinian input. Here are the main points and some of the most contested elements.
lead_paragraph: President Trump stood alongside Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel at the White House on Tuesday to reveal a long-awaited plan intended to resolve generations of conflict between Israelis and Palestinians.
